CLASS IX and X
ENGLISH COMPOSITION
LESSON 3 – PARAGRAPH WRITING
SOLUTION
EXERCISE
Write a Paragraph on each of the following:
1) An Accident
Ans: Last week I saw an accident. It is still fresh in my mind. A child was trying to cross the
road. A car came from the opposite direction. The driver tried to save the child. But a bus,
coming from the opposite direction ran into the car. The driver of the bus had only minor
injuries. The car driver was seriously injured. Some passengers of the bus also got light
injuries. Some went to inform the police and the seriously injured persons were sent to
hospital. It was a very shocking incident.
2) The Republic Day
Ans: Republic Day is the day when Constitution of India came into force in 1950 on 26
th
of
January. It is one of the most important national events for India and its citizens. It is
celebrated every year since 1950 and will be continued in the future forever to remember the
occurrence of Indian Constitution.
3) A School Function
Ans: The annual function of our school was held on 6
th
December. Preparations for the
function were made of few days in advance. The school building and the main hall was
decorated. The Director of Education was the Chief Guest. He presided over the function
and gave away the prizes. He congratulated the Principal and staff on the progress made by
the school. The Principal thanked the Chief Guest and the function came to a close with the
singing of the National Anthem.
4) Need for Education for all
Ans: Education means to understand and learn by exploring new adventures. The basic
education is necessary for everyone to know the difference between good and bad for them.
These days, education has reached every place, but still there are children who do not get
education. This is due to poverty. But this problem is no more with the society because the
Government has set up several Government Schools free of cost, where the school provides
children with midday meal. Education is for all and everyone has got the right to achieve it.
Page | 2
5) My favorite T.V. Serial
Ans: Television provides information and entertainment. It is also possible to see great
events happening anywhere in the world on the small T.V. screen. One of my favourite T.V.
Serial is a serial which is broadcasted on Star World. It revolves around the fight of good
and bad. In this serial, a twelve years old boy Finn, with his friend Tom, fights against the
evil. He tries to keep evil away from harming people.
6) A visit to the zoo
Ans: My friends and I visited the zoo. As we approached the main gate, we saw a huge
crowd. We entered the zoological garden and came across a beautiful lake in which some
aquatic birds like ducks and swans were swimming. It was a charming sight. In the next
enclosure, there were leopards, bears, eagles and tigers. After that, we came across a garden
in which stags and deer were frisking about. There were monkeys and baboons too. Their
tricks and pranks were very pleasing. As the sun was setting, we came out of the zoo. I shall
always remember my thrilling experience in the zoo.
7) A visit to a Book Fair
Ans: A book fair provided an excellent opportunity to one and all to buy the books of their
choice at one go. I have also visited a book fair organized in the Imphal Academy Campus.
Different publishers had put up their stalls and displayed their books in their stalls. A large
number of publishers including some international publishers like Macmillan, Orient,
Longman etc. was participating. Thousands of book – lovers all over the state visited the
book fair. Such book fairs should be organized every year in all major cities of the country.
8) An ideal student
Ans: An ideal student is one who is fully conscious of his responsibilities. A student may be
very good in his studies but he need not necessarily be an ideal student. An ideal student
should believe in simple living and high thinking. He student should believe in simple living
and high thinking. He is a model for others. He is fully aware of his duties and has some
good qualities. They are noble, studious and high-minded in their duties and brilliant in
studies. An ideal student is an asset to a school, society and to the nation as a whole.
9) A Scene in the Examination hall
Ans: The scene in the examination hall can be described best either by the invigilators or by
the examinees. An examination is commonly a silent place. Students remain busy writing
the answer to different questions. But nowadays the scene in an examination hall in not up
to satisfactory. The mentality of the students and their guardians has become corrupted.
They adopt unfair means to pass in the examination even though time is precious for one to
look right and left. The intelligent students become happy and time seems to pass within
minutes. The dull students feel bad, tense and worried.
Page | 3
10. School Morning Assembly
Ans: A School Morning Assembly is a gathering of all or part of a school for any variety of
purposes, such as special programs or communicating information on a daily or weekly
basis. In some schools, students gather to perform a common song or prayer and to receive
common announcements. It serves as powerful motivators for the entire school. Morning
assembly is a powerful way to instill discipline and also to set a joyful and focused tone for
the day.
11. Why I love my school
Ans: There are many reasons to love my school. It is our second home. My school is
incredibly unique as it gives us a sense of contributing something to the community and
can make a difference. I feel so comfortable there. Our teachers do anything to help
students succeed. I always have someone looking out for me at school. I have got many
friends at school and the people I have met at my school, have made such a huge impact on
me. My school offers so many different opportunities to get involved in things around the
campus. My school taught me moral values, and helps me become a better human being.
12. Why I love my Country
Ans: I love my country India, which is known for it rich cultural heritage and natural
resources. The natural beauty of India is enchanting. I especially love our best national
values; freedom opportunity, community, justice, human rights, and equality under the law
for all of our citizens of every race, creed, culture and gender, not just for the rich and
powerful, in particular, I love our tradition and history. I am proud of my nation. Above all,
India is my motherland.
13. When there is no Electricity
Ans: To think of life without electricity is almost impossible today. Electricity provides all
the comforts of life. We find ourselves completely helpless and feel its importance
whenever power fails or when the supply is irregular. Life would be totally different without
electricity. No electric appliances would have not been there. There would have not been so
many inventions in the field of health and treatment of diseases. Science and technology
would have not developed so much. Electricity has become an integral part of our life
stream.
Page | 4
14. Meeting an old friend
Ans: A true friend is a great gift of God. When we meet our old friend after a long time,
our joy knows no boundary. It is as if we have come upon a lost treasure. We start our
endless talks and asked one another about the welfare of our families. Both of us are
overjoyed and excited. It looks that our friendship has been cemented once more and
forever. We are both emotional and happy.
15. People who serve us.
Ans: There are many people around us who serve us daily and makes our life easy and
comfortable. Without them, life would not be very easy. Milkman, Newspaperman,
Sweeper, Postman, Bus conductor, driver, policeman, peons, washer man etc are some
persons who serve us daily. All these persons are low paid. They deserve our love, care
and attention. We should try to help them in whatever way it is possible.
16. Being a Teenager
Ans: In today’s world, being a teenager is not easy. There are many changes and
challenges to face, decisions to make and choose the roads to take. But at the same time,
it is fun. A teenager faces new experiences daily. This is one of most important stages of
life. During this stage of life, a person is most insecure of their physical appearance.
Teenagers make a big deal out of how they dress up. The company of friends sometimes
become more valuable than family. Peer pressure is at its peak. So, teenagers just need
acceptance, love and support from the people around them in order to get through.
17. How to study for Examination
Ans: Exam preparation really begins the day when your course begins, because our
success depends on our day-to-day study habits. We must have well-organised and
complete notes and have regular revision of our work at the end of each topic or section.
Above all, we must organize our time, make a study plan, organize our space (physical
and mental), organize our material, do some research, revise and test ourselves and make
our final preparations.
18. Social service
Ans: The service rendered by an individual or an institution to improve the social
conditions of society is called ‘social service.’ This service is rendered on humanitarian
considerations and without any motive of profit. Social service is based on the ideal of
brotherhood of man. It is a natural impulse to help man in distress. It cannot be rendered
without an element of self-service, to remove poverty and illiteracy, to help people in the
matters of sanitation, to reconstruct village roads, to clear slums, to plant trees, to give
relief to flood-stricken people are some of the social services.
Page | 5
19. My Neighbour
Ans: Neighbours play an important role in our social life. A good neighbour makes our
life sweet whereas bad neighbour makes a hell of it. One cannot have neighbours of
one’s choice. My neighbour lives just next to our house. They are really a nice family.
Their daughter Pinky is my friend. We have got good relation with our nighbour. Both
the families stand together in joy and sorrow. Neighbours play an important role in our
social life. We are fortunate to have a good neighbour.
20. The importance of Trees
Ans: We often get to hear ‘plant trees and save the Earth.’ This clearly indicates the
importance of trees to the well-being of our planet and is directly linked to our survival.
Trees are the best gift given by God. Tree provides oxygen to Billions of living being.
Tree provides us oxygen, beautiful flowers, fruits helpful leaves, woods, rubber, oils etc
for living beings. Trees are our life. We should protect and conserve them. We should
not cut trees in order to maintain the balance of environment.
